WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.089 --> 00:00:03.339
(gentle upbeat music)

00:00:11.260 --> 00:00:12.750
- So we often get the question,

00:00:12.750 --> 00:00:15.510
how does one get in the right position

00:00:15.510 --> 00:00:16.940
for a chest press?

00:00:16.940 --> 00:00:18.640
I'm gonna make it look easy.

00:00:18.640 --> 00:00:20.130
You're gonna need to practice

00:00:20.130 --> 00:00:21.840
this a little bit.

00:00:21.840 --> 00:00:23.740
I'm not intentionally making it look easy,

00:00:23.740 --> 00:00:26.350
I just do it every other day.

00:00:26.350 --> 00:00:27.640
Because I follow the program

00:00:27.640 --> 00:00:29.090
and I've been doing it for three years.

00:00:29.090 --> 00:00:32.040
So it's okay if you've got to try

00:00:32.040 --> 00:00:33.140
this a couple of times,

00:00:33.140 --> 00:00:35.270
but watch the video very carefully,

00:00:35.270 --> 00:00:37.300
because there's a lot of little nuances.

00:00:37.300 --> 00:00:39.700
So I'm just gonna take a black band,

00:00:39.700 --> 00:00:41.523
and we're gonna hook it.

00:00:45.440 --> 00:00:49.043
Hook it on the bar, like this.

00:00:56.040 --> 00:00:58.970
So, normal position.

00:00:58.970 --> 00:01:02.800
So you want to start by
grabbing not the bar,

00:01:02.800 --> 00:01:04.460
but the band.

00:01:04.460 --> 00:01:05.760
So everybody see that,

00:01:05.760 --> 00:01:06.980
this is a triangle.

00:01:06.980 --> 00:01:08.130
Now I'm going to grab it

00:01:08.130 --> 00:01:10.100
with I do with my right arm,

00:01:10.100 --> 00:01:11.963
I'm going to put it over my head.

00:01:13.268 --> 00:01:15.880
And I'm going to get it cross body

00:01:15.880 --> 00:01:20.831
so that it's parallel with how my body is.

00:01:20.831 --> 00:01:24.070
So I got as much slack here as here.

00:01:24.070 --> 00:01:25.500
So cross body,

00:01:25.500 --> 00:01:26.580
we all got that.

00:01:26.580 --> 00:01:28.160
Now what I'm going to do

00:01:28.160 --> 00:01:29.820
is I'm going to take this side,

00:01:29.820 --> 00:01:31.030
the upper side,

00:01:31.030 --> 00:01:33.520
and drop it down,

00:01:33.520 --> 00:01:38.050
so that the band is in between the deltoid

00:01:38.050 --> 00:01:39.610
and the tricep.

00:01:39.610 --> 00:01:42.730
So it's in this position,

00:01:42.730 --> 00:01:45.570
it's in the correct
position on the left side

00:01:45.570 --> 00:01:47.110
of my body, your right.

00:01:47.110 --> 00:01:49.950
Now I'm gonna drop the other arm through

00:01:51.230 --> 00:01:52.820
and I'm ready to do it.

00:01:52.820 --> 00:01:54.510
It's just sitting right in position.

00:01:54.510 --> 00:01:56.480
So all I have to do now

00:01:56.480 --> 00:01:57.810
is grab a hold of the bar

00:01:58.940 --> 00:02:02.100
and push away from myself.

00:02:02.100 --> 00:02:04.800
Now I also keep constant tension.

00:02:04.800 --> 00:02:07.150
You notice how it all goes slack

00:02:07.150 --> 00:02:09.010
at the bottom like this.

00:02:09.010 --> 00:02:10.600
So to do it right,

00:02:10.600 --> 00:02:12.010
you keep tension on it,

00:02:12.010 --> 00:02:13.260
which is actually going

00:02:13.260 --> 00:02:14.580
to stimulate more muscle growth.

00:02:14.580 --> 00:02:17.070
So just push away from yourself

00:02:17.070 --> 00:02:19.540
and keep constant tension

00:02:19.540 --> 00:02:21.393
until you can't do any reps anymore.

